On December 2, 2013, the President signed into law S. 1545, also known as the PEPFAR Stewardship and Oversight Act of 2013. This law reauthorizes and extends certain authorities related to combating global HIV/AIDS. It includes limitations on U.S. contributions to the Global Fund, funding allocation requirements for bilateral global HIV/AIDS assistance, and annual reports that establish targets for HIV prevention, treatment, and care on a country-by-country basis.